Three held over $90m Hong Kong gold heist
Chinese police have arrested three men in connection with the theft of $90 million in gold from Hong Kong, the biggest haul in the territory’s history.download film Phoenix Forgotten 2017 now
The China Daily says the three men were arrested in Guangdong, the Chinese province bordering the former British colony, and returned to Hong Kong.
The men are suspected of stealing 265 pieces of gold bullion weighing one kilogram each from a warehouse owned by a gold investment company in Hong Kong’s New Territories.film Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales online streaming
The suspects, two of whom worked for the company, escaped across the border.
Hong Kong police identified them and asked Guangdong authorities to detain them.
Police found most of the gold in a car on the Hong Kong side of the border.